540
00:52:16,258 --> 00:52:17,142
Rym: I'm gonna go do something else.

541
00:52:17,523 --> 00:52:25,672
Rym: But then I land back in hell and I really want to go talk to everybody, give a gift to someone, and like see what other plot things I might have uncovered.

542
00:52:26,514 --> 00:52:28,681
Scott: Yeah, and also unlock other, right?

543
00:52:28,701 --> 00:52:29,505
Scott: There's still more.

544
00:52:29,545 --> 00:52:31,677
Scott: It's gonna be different even though you've beaten the game.

545
00:52:31,737 --> 00:52:33,448
Scott: If you go on a run again, it's a roguelike.

546
00:52:33,488 --> 00:52:34,615
Scott: You know there's gonna be infinite runs.

547
00:52:34,655 --> 00:52:35,320
Scott: It's not a spoiler.

548
00:52:36,601 --> 00:52:39,653
Scott: The ending that you'll get, there's like more and more endings.

549
00:52:39,753 --> 00:52:43,064
Scott: So the more times you beat the game, you get more stuff there.

550
00:52:43,084 --> 00:52:47,155
Scott: And also, there's just new things to do.

551
00:52:47,536 --> 00:52:52,113
Scott: You haven't run out of things until you've beaten the game many, many, many times, right?

552
00:52:52,795 --> 00:52:53,679
Scott: I only beat it once.

553
00:52:53,799 --> 00:52:58,337
Scott: I didn't beat it many, many times, but it still felt like a lot was there left to do.

554
00:52:58,397 --> 00:52:59,120
Scott: if I go back to it.

555
00:52:59,300 --> 00:53:03,820
Rym: Yep, like the plot that you uncover, you start to feel like, oh, I see where this is all going.

556
00:53:04,281 --> 00:53:12,043
Rym: All I'm going to say is it is surprisingly complex, and there's a lot going on you can unlock in this game.

557
00:53:12,063 --> 00:53:13,970
Scott: It's a Greek mythology plot, right?

558
00:53:14,030 --> 00:53:17,341
Rym: But I also appreciate how it's not super dialogue heavy.

559
00:53:17,402 --> 00:53:25,235
Rym: It's like you'll see an interaction, and like the interactions are just very interesting and pleasant, but they also don't overstay their welcome.

560
00:53:25,255 --> 00:53:28,329
Rym: It's not like you're reading just like pages and pages of lore.

561
00:53:28,429 --> 00:53:30,337
Rym: It's like, well, Medusa, you have different conversations.

562
00:53:31,961 --> 00:53:34,630
Scott: Yep, I don't read pages and pages of lore, right?

563
00:53:34,790 --> 00:53:41,160
Scott: It's basically sort of like the amount of text you'd get in a Zelda game, but only with voice acting instead of, ah!

564
00:53:41,620 --> 00:53:48,892
Rym: Yep, and you have fun little bits like I got my Artemis really up, and then I started getting my Ares really up, and the two of them are kind of low-key beefing.

565
00:53:49,293 --> 00:53:53,369
Rym: And now that beefing kind of happens in the dialogue I have.

566
00:53:53,449 --> 00:53:57,462
Rym: Ares will be like, ah, you've got that stink of her on you again.

567
00:53:59,346 --> 00:54:09,209
Rym: Like fun stuff happens, and it's interesting enough to keep you playing the game even when you really should go to bed, even if you would have stopped.

568
00:54:10,453 --> 00:54:16,178
Rym: And you can even give a gift to Skelly, the skeleton whose sole purpose is to learn a new weapon when you get it.

569
00:54:18,345 --> 00:54:25,311
Scott: Yep, so the only thing I want to say about this game is the only negative is that there's no multiplayer, right?

570
00:54:25,352 --> 00:54:30,170
Scott: This is the best of games I've played, of action RPGs I've played, right?

571
00:54:30,230 --> 00:54:32,499
Rym: Oh, if I could play co-op in this game...

572
00:54:33,061 --> 00:54:37,079
Scott: Right, just forget about the roguelike parts of the game, forget about all that stuff.

573
00:54:37,139 --> 00:54:49,319
Scott: Just the way the character controls action RPG-wise, right, is better than like any... It's like better than a Zelda, better than a Secret of Mana, better than any...

574
00:54:50,042 --> 00:54:52,050
Rym: The frame timing just feels right.

575
00:54:52,210 --> 00:54:54,760
Rym: When you get hit, it's your own goddamn fault.

576
00:54:55,120 --> 00:54:56,343
Rym: Nothing feels cheesy.

577
00:54:57,346 --> 00:55:04,343
Scott: Nope, it's like there isn't another action RPG that controls as perfectly and nicely as this one does.

578
00:55:04,363 --> 00:55:13,964
Scott: I really wish there was a co-op way to play just with an action RPG that controls like this one.

579
00:55:14,365 --> 00:55:23,817
Scott: Just take the controls from this game and maybe the art style, the 3/4 review, I guess, and just make another action RPG that's a co-op one.

580
00:55:23,837 --> 00:55:26,410
Scott: There's tons of co-op action RPGs out there, but they're all kind of meh.

581
00:55:26,470 --> 00:55:36,944
Rym: If I had to articulate it, it's that like hit boxes and what damages you is like the right level, coupled with, like I said earlier, it's almost a puzzle.

582
00:55:37,065 --> 00:55:38,130
Rym: It is execution.

583
00:55:38,150 --> 00:55:40,620
Rym: You have to time things and jump around, and it's an action game.

584
00:55:40,640 --> 00:55:43,471
Scott: And you can actually see what's going on, right?

585
00:55:43,632 --> 00:55:45,419
Scott: You can see things and dodge them.

586
00:55:46,302 --> 00:55:49,252
Rym: But you can play this game without ever getting hit.

587
00:55:49,312 --> 00:55:54,029
Rym: You can treat it like a puzzle that requires you to execute to solve the puzzle.

588
00:55:54,370 --> 00:55:56,840
Rym: And a lot of action RPGs really fail in that regard.

589
00:55:57,360 --> 00:56:00,134
Scott: And you encounter enemies that you've encountered on previous runs.

590
00:56:00,174 --> 00:56:02,123
Scott: You know how those enemies behave, right?

591
00:56:02,143 --> 00:56:09,373
Scott: So for example, there's a room in the lava area that you can get sometimes where there's a bunch of witches that shoot lots and lots of projectiles everywhere, right?

592
00:56:10,016 --> 00:56:19,457
Scott: So if you have a deflect ability, that room can be so easy because you deflect all these projectiles and they go right back to where they came from and you beat it in two seconds.

593
00:56:19,598 --> 00:56:20,622
Rym: But you know what I started doing?

594
00:56:21,285 --> 00:56:32,003
Rym: I used to focus on upgrades that like complemented my own actual skills in the game, but I realized that what I needed to do is focus on the upgrades that cover for the things I am dog shit at.

595
00:56:32,785 --> 00:56:41,512
Scott: Anyway, but the point is if you don't have deflect and you get in that room and it's like a bullet hell situation, right?

596
00:56:41,652 --> 00:56:42,937
Scott: And it's like, yeah, it's the same room.

597
00:56:42,957 --> 00:56:44,685
Scott: You encountered it two runs ago, right?

598
00:56:44,705 --> 00:56:51,609
Scott: You know this room, but because you have a completely different, you know, loadout this time, you didn't get any deflect abilities.

599
00:56:51,850 --> 00:56:59,937
Scott: You have to figure out using the abilities that you've got, how are you going to deal with this bullet hell room?

600
00:57:00,378 --> 00:57:02,529
Scott: How are you going to dodge all these things and not get killed?

601
00:57:02,549 --> 00:57:03,897
Scott: Because it could be super dangerous.

602
00:57:03,977 --> 00:57:09,557
